      <body>Let me clarify:
I was envisioning augmenting the current system wherein fields are declared in the controllers.

That is:

app/controllers/application.rb:
@@@ ruby
class ApplicationController &lt; ActionController::base
  filter_parameter_logging :password, :ssn, ...
  ...
end
@@@

config/environments/development.rb:
@@@ ruby
config.action_controller.filter_parameter_logging = false
# or even
config.action_controller.filter_parameter_logging = []
@@@

By default, the filtering would be on, leaving the Controllers to dictate the behavior.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Let me clarify:
I was envisioning augmenting the current system wherein fields are declared in the controllers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;app/controllers/application.rb:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;
class ApplicationController &amp;lt; ActionController::base
  filter_parameter_logging :password, :ssn, ...
  ...
end
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;config/environments/development.rb:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;
config.action_controller.filter_parameter_logging = false
# or even
config.action_controller.filter_parameter_logging = []
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By default, the filtering would be on, leaving the Controllers to dictate the behavior.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
